 {"id":"asupersync-6cl","title":"[fastapi-integration] 2.2: Lab Runtime for Deterministic HTTP Testing","description":"# 2.2: Lab Runtime for Deterministic HTTP Testing

## Objective
Enable deterministic testing of HTTP handlers using Asupersync's lab runtime, making race conditions and timing bugs reproducible.

## Background

### The Problem with Non-Deterministic Tests
```rust
// Flaky test: passes sometimes, fails sometimes
#[tokio::test]
async fn test_concurrent_requests() {
    let server = start_server().await;

    // Race condition: order depends on scheduling
    let (a, b) = tokio::join!(
        client.get("/a"),
        client.get("/b"),
    );

    // Might fail due to timing issues
    assert!(a.is_ok() && b.is_ok());
}
```

### The Asupersync Solution
```rust
// Deterministic test: same seed -> same behavior
#[test]
fn test_concurrent_requests() {
    let lab = LabRuntime::with_seed(12345);

    lab.block_on(async {
        let server = VirtualServer::bind(&lab, "localhost:8080");

        // Deterministic: lab controls scheduling order
        let (a, b) = join(
            lab.client().get("http://localhost:8080/a"),
            lab.client().get("http://localhost:8080/b"),
        ).await;

        assert!(a.is_ok() && b.is_ok());
    });

    // If this fails, running with same seed reproduces EXACTLY
}
```

## Requirements

### 1. Virtual HTTP Server
```rust
/// HTTP server backed by lab runtime's virtual network.
pub struct VirtualServer {
    listener: VirtualTcpListener,
    router: Router,
}

impl VirtualServer {
    /// Bind to virtual address in lab runtime.
    pub fn bind(lab: &LabRuntime, addr: &str) -> Self {
        let listener = lab.virtual_tcp_listener(addr.parse().unwrap());
        Self { listener, router: Router::new() }
    }

    /// Add route handler.
    pub fn route(mut self, path: &str, handler: impl Handler) -> Self {
        self.router.add(path, handler);
        self
    }

    /// Serve requests (runs in lab runtime).
    pub async fn serve(&self, cx: &Cx<'_>) -> Outcome<!, ServerError> {
        loop {
            let (stream, addr) = self.listener.accept(cx).await?;
            cx.spawn(self.handle_connection(stream, addr));
        }
    }
}
```

### 2. Virtual HTTP Client
```rust
